title: Dutch eventing draws 60,000 spectators
text: > Sports Dutch eventing draws 60,000 spectators Arnaud Boiteau of the French riding academy Cadre Noir de Saumur and his horse Sultan de la Motte kick up water after a jump followed by a large tray of water during the cross-country discipline of the Military Boekelo, eastern Netherlands, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015. The cross-country, a 6 kilometer long trail (3.72 miles) is designed by Olympic course designer Sue Benson and is part of Eventing, or horse trial, a three-discipline equestrian event of a single horse and rider combination which consists of dressage, cross-country and show jumping. (AP Photo/Peter Dejong)
